HEADWORD: Oviform
<hw>O"vi*form</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"v⟦icr⟧*f⟦ocir⟧rm)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ov</ets>um + <ets>-form</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>oviforme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having the form or
figure of an egg; egg-shaped; <as>as, an <ex>oviform</ex>
leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ovoid, ovoidal.</syn>⟦br⟧
